{
  "version": 2,
  "_comment_schema": "FlexBoard Pro v1.11+ schema. Each user under 'approved' MAY include an optional 'plan_until' field (ISO-8601 UTC timestamp). Rules: (a) plan_until missing OR null => LIFETIME access. (b) plan_until in the FUTURE => approved, app shows live countdown. (c) plan_until in the PAST => PlanExpired, keyboard locks and Plans screen opens. (d) ID under 'blocked' => instant lock (wins over approved). The 3-day free trial is local — no entry needed.",
  "_comment_workflow": "Add a user after they pay via WhatsApp: copy their android_id (they get it on the Plans screen / lock screen and it arrives in the WhatsApp message), pick the right plan_until based on plan: monthly = +30 days, 6mo = +180 days, yearly = +365 days. Use UTC. Lifetime users (e.g. you / testers) — set plan_until to null. The app re-checks every ~5 minutes, so changes here go live within minutes.",
  "_comment_blocking": "To revoke a user, EITHER remove their entry from 'approved' OR (recommended) move it into 'blocked'. Blocked wins over approved, so 'blocked' is safer if you might re-add the user later.",
  "_comment_names": "All 'name' fields are placeholders ('xyz'). Replace with the actual buyer name from their WhatsApp message before saving — this just helps you keep track of who paid.",
